        "stop": "Englehart",
        "category": "Nature",
        "desc": "One of Northeastern Ontario's most accessible wilderness gems. Kap-Kig-Iwan means 'steep rocks' in Ojibway - a name earned by the dramatic Englehart River gorge and 10-metre waterfall at the park's heart. Swim in the natural rock pools above the falls, hike the gorge trail, and camp under towering old-growth pines. An easy day trip from Englehart station or an overnight stay. One of Ontario's most underrated provincial parks.",
